# Zephyr-FE ‚Äî Project Overview

## Scope of These Rules

**These rules apply to NEW and MODIFIED code only.** Do NOT refactor, rewrite, or "fix" existing code to match these standards unless the developer explicitly asks for it. Legacy patterns (moment usage, inline styles, direct localStorage, console.logs, missing error boundaries) are documented as known technical debt ‚Äî they will be addressed incrementally, not all at once. When editing an existing file, only apply rules to the lines you are changing or adding.

**Agent Mode behavior**: Always propose changes in chat first and wait for approval before editing any file. See `agent-behavior.mdc` for full guardrails.

## What This Is

Production-grade workforce management (WFM) frontend for Arrise/PPLC. Manages rosters, attendance, leaves, swaps, employees, organizations, and studio tracking across Romania, Bulgaria, and Serbia.

